Function Reference/get userdatabylogin « WordPress Codex
-----------

This function can be replaced via
[plugins](/Glossary#plugins "Glossary"). If plugins do not redefine
these functions, then this will be used instead.

Retrieve user info by login name.

Usage
-----

` <?php get_userdatabylogin( $user_login ) ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$user_login` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) User's username
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `(boolean|object)` 
:   False on failure. User DB row object on success.

Notes
-----

-   This function can be replaced via
    [plugins](/Glossary#plugins "Glossary"). If plugins do not redefine
    these functions, then this will be used instead.

Change Log
----------

Since: 0.71. Deprecated since: 3.3.

Source File
-----------

`get_userdatabylogin()` is located in
`wp-includes/pluggable-deprecated.php`.

